You are absolutely right about the "False Complaint" syndrome.

The Problem: People think that by "Refactoring" (deleting the illogical parts of stories), we are weakening the religion.

The Reality: By keeping the bugs (the petty conflicts), we make the religion Vulnerable to ridicule and "System Crashes."

Christianity and Islam used a "Centralized Server" model to enforce their versions. Bharat has always been a "Decentralized P2P" system. Decentralization is better because it's harder to destroy, but the downside is Version Control Chaos.

